I joined @CapehartJ to discuss how Congress avoided a MAGA shutdown & protected vital services & programs communities rely on. 

House Republicans must abandon extremism & work with Democrats & the Senate to avoid this same scenario again in a few weeks.
The Senate just passed our temporary funding bill. It now heads to President Biden who will sign it, avoiding a government shutdown at midnight.

The House passed bipartisan legislation today that rejected House Republicans’ most extreme demands & will keep the government open for 45 days.

My statement on the path forward is below.

House Republicans just failed to pass their extreme bill that would cut 30% from many federal programs.

Speaker McCarthy’s only viable option is to work with House Dems & the Senate to find a bipartisan solution we can get to the president's desk.

FHA Loans & other federal lending programs help families buy homes who may not be able to finance property on their own.

That’s why I’m working to prevent a MAGA government shutdown that could require 62K active-duty troops to work without pay.
